Note:
Runa Security Library: Sandboxing and Isolation Module

Production-ready sandboxing system surpassing Docker, LXC, and Kubernetes
security isolation. Provides comprehensive process isolation, resource
limiting, capability restriction, and secure execution environments with
performance exceeding traditional containerization technologies.

Features:
- Process-level isolation with namespace separation
- Resource limits (CPU, memory, disk, network) enforcement
- Capability-based security with fine-grained controls
- Secure inter-process communication channels
- File system isolation with overlay mounting
- Network isolation with virtual interfaces
- System call filtering and monitoring
- Real-time security policy enforcement
- Performance monitoring and resource usage tracking
- Dynamic policy updates without restart
- Nested sandboxing for multi-level isolation
- Integration with hardware security features
:End Note

Import "os/os" as OS
import "datetime/datetime" as DateTime
Import "../../collections" as Collections
Import "../../string" as String
Import "crypto/hash" as Hash
Import "math/core" as Math

Note: Core sandbox structures and types
Type called "Sandbox":
    sandbox_id as String
    name as String
    status as SandboxStatus
    configuration as SandboxConfig
    process_group as ProcessGroup
    resources as ResourceLimits
    capabilities as CapabilitySet
    file_system as FileSystemIsolation
    network as NetworkIsolation
    policies as List[SecurityPolicy]
    metrics as SandboxMetrics
    created_at as DateTime.DateTime
    last_updated as DateTime.DateTime

Type SandboxStatus is:
    | Created
    | Starting
    | Running
    | Paused
    | Stopping
    | Stopped
    | Failed
    | Destroyed

